                Group 6<br>
        <br>
Coordination instructions: All coordination will be directed by the General, do not move with out the say so of him. Seriously people, if this thing goes bad, you all will want to know who to blame so be courteous and do as you are told<br>
<br>
Service and Support: Everyone is required to bring a 30plat minimum to give to another player. You pick the player to give it to, but you must bring and then give away the 30plat. All participants are expected to be at level 45 the day of the raid with 80FR and 60MR, no lying either. All loot will fall under the Guild Alliance rules as in accordance with the rules posted on the Guild Alliance home page.<br>
<br>
Command and Signal: Only the Raid General, the Colonel, and the Captains (Group Leaders), will use the OOC channel. All complaints and suggestions will be directed to the Colonel (Looking for an experienced volunteer) and then filtered to the General as needed. Do not use the shout channel and also please turn off all of your BS responses, ie Damage shields, attack amounts and damage taken, you don’t need to know if you hit Naggy for 100hp, but you do need to know if your Cleric is about to die, so please comply with this directive. <br>
<br>
Appendixes<br>
